00:28:01,466 --> 00:28:03,739
You're not the only one in
the line of fire here.

525
00:28:03,740 --> 00:28:05,836
What happened to Gregory Malina?

526
00:28:07,460 --> 00:28:11,031
Looks like our boy Gregory Malina's
going to be deposed after all.

527
00:28:13,619 --> 00:28:15,747
Make sure it doesn't
get screwed up this time.

528
00:28:17,890 --> 00:28:19,455
I'll do it myself.

529
00:28:20,268 --> 00:28:21,894
I thought you didn't want to know.

530
00:28:21,895 --> 00:28:23,322
I do now.

531
00:28:46,824 --> 00:28:49,045
Excuse me. Sorry.

532
00:28:50,452 --> 00:28:52,597
- What's his name?
- Theo.

533
00:28:54,365 --> 00:28:56,563
Miss Hewes, when we were in your office,

534
00:28:56,564 --> 00:28:58,911
were you suggesting
that I should fire him?

535
00:28:59,099 --> 00:29:00,099
Why?

536
00:29:00,804 --> 00:29:01,804
You want to fire him?

537
00:29:02,744 --> 00:29:05,169
He just started. I thought
I should give him some time.

538
00:29:05,170 --> 00:29:07,476
He's your assistant.
Do what you want.

539
00:29:08,444 --> 00:29:10,022
Anything jumping out at you?

540
00:29:10,554 --> 00:29:11,602
Not yet.

541
00:29:11,603 --> 00:29:14,231
There is an official from the S.E.C

542
00:29:14,247 --> 00:29:16,455
who was aggressive in
going after Frobisher's company.

543
00:29:16,456 --> 00:29:18,554
Tom and I thought he
might be worth talking to.

544
00:29:18,555 --> 00:29:19,555
His name?

545
00:29:19,556 --> 00:29:20,949
George Moore.

546
00:29:21,261 --> 00:29:23,450
I don't think there's anything there.

547
00:29:23,451 --> 00:29:26,299
Moore was interviewed extensively
for the government trial.

548
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:27,838
I thought we'd just pick his brain.

549
00:29:27,839 --> 00:29:30,514
If Tom thinks it's useful,
it's fine with me.

550
00:29:31,434 --> 00:29:34,482
Miss Hewes, is it okay if tomorrow
I step out for a few hours?

551
00:29:34,798 --> 00:29:36,018
What for?

552
00:29:36,049 --> 00:29:38,441
My father hit a woman with his car.

553
00:29:38,442 --> 00:29:41,439
He's being deposed, and
I thought that I should be there.

554
00:29:42,018 --> 00:29:43,629
Well, of course.

555
00:29:44,459 --> 00:29:45,718
Is he at fault?

556
00:29:46,187 --> 00:29:47,457
He seems to think so.

557
00:29:47,458 --> 00:29:50,478
I mean, he's the kind of guy who
likes to take responsibility.

558
00:29:50,647 --> 00:29:51,664
Better be careful.

559
00:29:51,665 --> 00:29:54,527
We plaintiff attorneys can be vicious.

560
00:29:55,427 --> 00:29:57,475
His best strategy is
to blame the victim.

561
00:29:57,664 --> 00:29:58,679
I know.

562
00:29:58,680 --> 00:30:02,305
At all costs. It was her fault, period.

563
00:30:05,654 --> 00:30:08,766
He's in the bathroom, but
he'll be back in a minute.

564
00:30:09,861 --> 00:30:11,739
I'm so sorry to interrupt your dinner.

565
00:30:14,023 --> 00:30:15,556
Hello. You must be chloe.

566
00:30:15,900 --> 00:30:17,246
Patty Hewes.

567
00:30:17,247 --> 00:30:19,477
And Rob. Hello.

568
00:30:19,478 --> 00:30:21,174
What are you doing here?

569
00:30:21,175 --> 00:30:22,485
I was in the neighborhood.

570
00:30:22,486 --> 00:30:24,099
Thought I'd meet the family.

571
00:30:24,100 --> 00:30:25,961
Now is not a good time.

572
00:30:26,133 --> 00:30:27,931
How about I come by the office Tomorrow?

573
00:30:27,932 --> 00:30:30,045
Ah, afraid it can't wait, Larry.

574
00:30:30,733 --> 00:30:32,865
Ray Fiske came to see me.

575
00:30:33,459 --> 00:30:35,165
He offered a settlement.

576
00:30:35,259 --> 00:30:36,572
Hey, that's terrific.

577
00:30:36,573 --> 00:30:38,279
$175 million.

578
00:30:42,454 --> 00:30:44,464
Should we take it?

579
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,466
Why are you asking me?

580
00:30:46,467 --> 00:30:49,085
Because 175 is a...

581
00:30:49,758 --> 00:30:51,213
interesting number.

582
00:30:52,809 --> 00:30:54,790
I don't know what you're implying.

583
00:30:55,619 --> 00:30:57,294
You've been talking to the other side.

584
00:30:57,295 --> 00:30:58,968
- Are you nuts?
- No,

585
00:30:59,593 --> 00:31:00,877
you don't want to do that.

586
00:31:01,049 --> 00:31:03,472
Don't speak without a
criminal attorney present.

587
00:31:03,694 --> 00:31:05,617
You're already facing three to five.

588
00:31:05,618 --> 00:31:08,026
How dare you come in here and
hijack me with accusations?

589
00:31:08,027 --> 00:31:10,197
Yeah, the truth is, Larry, I like you,

590
00:31:10,776 --> 00:31:12,445
but I think you're in over your head,

591
00:31:12,446 --> 00:31:15,754
and prison is the last
place where you belong.

592
00:31:16,756 --> 00:31:18,757
Arthur frobisher is smart.

593
00:31:18,758 --> 00:31:21,447
I'm sure he's got a way to
get you your blood money,

594
00:31:21,448 --> 00:31:23,349
with no paper trail, so

595
00:31:23,350 --> 00:31:26,102
I'm really just here tonight
to make you a promise.

596
00:31:26,321 --> 00:31:28,484
Oh, yeah? What's that?

597
00:31:29,607 --> 00:31:31,364
I'm going to wait and watch...

598
00:31:32,146 --> 00:31:33,695
until you buy a house,

599
00:31:34,086 --> 00:31:36,277
or mildred buys a car, or...

600
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:38,232
chloe here buys a toothbrush.

601
00:31:39,171 --> 00:31:41,292
You need to understand this, Larry,

602
00:31:42,231 --> 00:31:46,429
no popler for the next hundred years
will be able to spend

603
00:31:46,430 --> 00:31:48,260
a nickel of that money

604
00:31:48,322 --> 00:31:52,310
without being humiliated,
disgraced and locked up.

605
00:31:58,939 --> 00:32:00,645
You all have a nice night.

606
00:32:18,474 --> 00:32:19,866
How do you plea?

607
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,243
Not guilty.

608
00:32:23,448 --> 00:32:25,342
Not a flight risk, your honor.

609
00:32:25,343 --> 00:32:26,780
No prior criminal record.

610
00:32:26,781 --> 00:32:28,643
An upstanding member of the community.

611
00:32:28,815 --> 00:32:31,719
Bail is set at $1.5 million.

612
00:32:32,142 --> 00:32:33,483
Next.

613
00:32:36,225 --> 00:32:38,758
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

614
00:32:38,759 --> 00:32:41,445
and nothing but the
truth, so help you god?

615
00:32:41,446 --> 00:32:42,581
I do.

616
00:32:44,446 --> 00:32:48,349
And when you pulled even with the
stop sign, did you see Miss Reynolds?

617
00:32:49,241 --> 00:32:50,443
Yes.

618
00:32:50,444 --> 00:32:53,490
She was standing to my left,
about ten feet away.

619
00:32:53,727 --> 00:32:55,823
Did you see miss reynolds
walk towards your vehicle?

620
00:32:55,824 --> 00:32:56,824
No.

621
00:32:56,885 --> 00:32:58,449
Not even out of the corner of your eye?

622
00:32:58,450 --> 00:33:00,087
Move on. You already said no.

623
00:33:01,761 --> 00:33:03,106
Mr. Parsons...

624
00:33:04,577 --> 00:33:07,596
what was your general state of
mind leading up to the accident?

625
00:33:08,050 --> 00:33:10,125
How about being a little more specific?

626
00:33:10,442 --> 00:33:12,973
Were you upset? Angry?

627
00:33:17,635 --> 00:33:20,002
Well, just before it happened,

628
00:33:20,299 --> 00:33:21,300
my wife and I...

629
00:33:21,301 --> 00:33:23,272
May we take five minutes, please?

630
00:33:26,339 --> 00:33:29,106
Mr. Parsons, I told you before,

631
00:33:29,107 --> 00:33:31,254
no one needs to know
your emotional state or

632
00:33:31,255 --> 00:33:33,194
that your attention was somewhere else.

633
00:33:33,195 --> 00:33:35,442
My wife and I were arguing.
I'm telling them what happened.

634
00:33:35,443 --> 00:33:37,460
- And as your attorney...
- You're not his attorney.

635
00:33:37,461 --> 00:33:39,625
You represent his insurance company.

636
00:33:39,750 --> 00:33:41,690
I'd like a moment with my father.

637
00:33:43,161 --> 00:33:45,195
Dad, he's right.

638
00:33:45,298 --> 00:33:46,643
You agree with that creep?

639
00:33:46,644 --> 00:33:49,272
Your policy only covers $200 000.

640
00:33:49,538 --> 00:33:52,041
- If the plaintiff is awarded...
- She has a name--

641
00:33:52,245 --> 00:33:53,474
Linda Reynolds.

642
00:33:53,475 --> 00:33:56,312
If you admit fault and
she's awarded more than $200, 000,

643
00:33:56,313 --> 00:33:57,719
you're personally liable.

644
00:33:57,720 --> 00:34:00,073
- It was my fault.
- It was an accident.

645
00:34:02,795 --> 00:34:04,482
If that's work, you should go.

646
00:34:05,652 --> 00:34:08,108
Look, this guy isn't even
fighting for me anyway.

647
00:34:08,296 --> 00:34:10,913
He's just trying to save his company
money by refusing

648
00:34:10,914 --> 00:34:13,415
to pay linda's medical expenses.
Why should I help him?

649
00:34:13,416 --> 00:34:16,810
Because she's got a lawyer who's
going to go after every penny he can.

650
00:34:16,811 --> 00:34:18,437
So I should just go in there and lie?

651
00:34:18,438 --> 00:34:19,764
I'm saying that they will.

652
00:34:19,765 --> 00:34:21,768
They'll spin into gross negligence.

653
00:34:21,987 --> 00:34:23,473
This is the real world, dad.

654
00:34:24,506 --> 00:34:28,015
I don't need you to teach me
about the real world.

655
00:34:30,018 --> 00:34:31,504
I swore under oath.

656
00:34:32,771 --> 00:34:35,463
But you're the lawyer, Ellen,
tell me what to do.

657
00:34:35,464 --> 00:34:38,396
I've told you what
to do again and again.

658
00:34:42,962 --> 00:34:44,479
Mr. Parsons,

659
00:34:45,043 --> 00:34:48,187
what was your general state
of mind leading up to the accident?

660
00:35:05,885 --> 00:35:08,106
Thank you for seeing me again.

661
00:35:08,232 --> 00:35:10,406
Well, thank you for calling, Larry.

662
00:35:10,407 --> 00:35:12,121
I was sick about the other night.

663
00:35:12,122 --> 00:35:13,868
That was a terrible thing that happened.

664
00:35:13,869 --> 00:35:16,060
Nah, I should apologize to you.

665
00:35:16,061 --> 00:35:17,655
It's just I got all these pressures.

666
00:35:17,656 --> 00:35:19,486
I get it, I get it.

667
00:35:20,722 --> 00:35:24,076
Larry, the truth is, my attorney
doesn't even want me talking to you,

668
00:35:24,077 --> 00:35:27,878
so I'm not going to be able to
make good until after the trial.

669
00:35:27,925 --> 00:35:30,757
I understand, and i can hold
out. Just don't forget about me.

670
00:35:31,437 --> 00:35:32,452
Please...

671
00:35:33,172 --> 00:35:34,737
don't cut me out.

672
00:35:36,207 --> 00:35:38,490
Oh, that other thing, the witness?

673
00:35:38,929 --> 00:35:40,072
I'm looking into it.

674
00:35:40,697 --> 00:35:41,697
Thank you.

675
00:35:43,228 --> 00:35:44,917
You know who you remind me of,
don't you?

676
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:47,640
My dad.

677
00:35:48,297 --> 00:35:49,752
That means a lot.

678
00:35:50,174 --> 00:35:52,584
Guys like you are what make
this country great, Larry.

679
00:36:03,025 --> 00:36:05,175
The guy from the sec wants to push
up our meeting.

680
00:36:05,254 --> 00:36:06,427
You ready in ten?

681
00:36:06,615 --> 00:36:07,615
Sure.

682
00:36:10,698 --> 00:36:13,796
Mom. What happened.
What's going on?

683
00:36:15,297 --> 00:36:18,161
Your father wouldn't call you,
but I thought you should know.

684
00:36:18,239 --> 00:36:19,256
Know what?

685
00:36:19,257 --> 00:36:22,062
They're not just suing us
for hospital bills anymore.

686
00:36:23,376 --> 00:36:24,376
It's okay.

687
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:28,185
This woman's hurt worse
then they thought,

688
00:36:28,186 --> 00:36:29,749
and she may never work again.

689
00:36:30,172 --> 00:36:31,579
How much are they asking for?

690
00:36:31,580 --> 00:36:34,075
Over a million dollars.

691
00:36:34,492 --> 00:36:36,250
They can't do that, can they?

692
00:36:36,251 --> 00:36:38,923
I mean, they can't just say
we owe them all that money.

693
00:36:39,064 --> 00:36:40,753
Yeah, mom, they can.

694
00:36:44,471 --> 00:36:47,467
Your father didn't have to
tell them we were arguing.

695
00:36:48,740 --> 00:36:50,488
Car's here.

696
00:36:59,251 --> 00:37:01,175
Your mom called earlier.

697
00:37:01,176 --> 00:37:03,397
I just... it's my fault.

698
00:37:03,398 --> 00:37:06,467
I didn't have a chance
to... tell you earlier.

699
00:37:06,651 --> 00:37:07,668
It's fine.

700
00:37:12,370 --> 00:37:14,091
You know what?

701
00:37:14,827 --> 00:37:16,751
It's not fine. You're fired.

702
00:37:26,734 --> 00:37:28,611
<i>- Where are they taking her?
- Rikers island.</i>

703
00:37:29,314 --> 00:37:31,455
What will it cost to post bond?

704
00:37:33,451 --> 00:37:36,392
We can't afford that.
Not after the settlement

705
00:37:38,515 --> 00:37:41,018
This guy worked for the S.E.C.

706
00:37:41,221 --> 00:37:42,895
who tried to take down Frobisher.

707
00:37:43,344 --> 00:37:44,484
Really?

708
00:37:46,791 --> 00:37:49,017
We're looking for Mr. Moore.

709
00:37:51,771 --> 00:37:52,913
Hello there.

710
00:37:53,289 --> 00:37:54,744
Oh, Tom shayes.

711
00:37:55,182 --> 00:37:56,261
Ellen parsons.

712
00:37:56,262 --> 00:37:58,440
The pleasure's mine.
Come on in. Take a seat.

713
00:37:58,441 --> 00:37:59,580
Thank you.

714
00:38:01,597 --> 00:38:03,492
Hey, Larry, you got a second?

715
00:38:03,907 --> 00:38:05,112
Listen, I want to...

716
00:38:05,253 --> 00:38:08,867
I want to reassure you
that thing with the witness...

717
00:38:09,023 --> 00:38:12,355
I looked into it, and I can personally
guarantee you that

718
00:38:12,653 --> 00:38:14,483
Gregory Malina is safe.

719
00:38:14,780 --> 00:38:16,157
I'm glad to hear that.

720
00:38:16,158 --> 00:38:19,457
Yeah, evidently he had his own
reasons for not wanting to testify;

721
00:38:19,458 --> 00:38:21,804
drugs or something like that.

722
00:38:22,070 --> 00:38:23,469
I shouldn't have accused you.

723
00:38:23,470 --> 00:38:24,788
<i>No, it all right.</i>

724
00:38:25,226 --> 00:38:27,698
- All right, I'll talk to you later.
- <i>OK.</i>

725
00:38:30,812 --> 00:38:32,877
He says Gregory Malina is alive.

726
00:38:32,939 --> 00:38:34,481
Do you believe him?

727
00:38:34,817 --> 00:38:35,817
Do you?

728
00:38:36,462 --> 00:38:38,490
Well, we're going to find out.

729
00:38:43,031 --> 00:38:45,861
I'm glad you and I could
come to an arrangement, Larry.

730
00:38:46,847 --> 00:38:47,847
Me, too.

731
00:38:48,990 --> 00:38:51,228
Whatever I could do
to make things right.

732
00:39:18,975 --> 00:39:20,148
Please don't do this.

733
00:39:20,149 --> 00:39:21,322
You decide right now...

734
00:39:21,323 --> 00:39:23,825
do you want us or do you want this job?

735
00:39:24,232 --> 00:39:25,232
Right...

736
00:39:25,343 --> 00:39:26,438
now!

737
00:39:32,360 --> 00:39:34,113
We're done, Ellen.

738
00:39:58,450 --> 00:40:01,490
Hey, it's me. I'm so sorry.

739
00:40:02,174 --> 00:40:04,036
Just please...

740
00:40:04,552 --> 00:40:06,288
call me back, okay?

